Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan and Ireland are playing their final group game in the T20 World Cup.
Pakistan has never been eliminated so early from a T20 World Cup.
Ireland has lost four successive completed T20 World Cup games, their worst run since 2009-2012.
Pakistan may give Abrar Ahmed and Abbas Afridi a start.

Ireland's probable lineup includes Andy Balbirnie, Paul Stirling (capt), Lorcan Tucker (wk), Harry Tector, Curtis Campher, George Dockrell, Gareth Delany, Mark Adair, Barry McCarthy, Josh Little, and Craig Young/Ben White.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is scheduled for Lauderhill, Florida, on June 16, 2024, at 10:30am local time.
There were washouts in Lauderhill on Friday and Saturday due to weather conditions.
